                        <interp inst="t18410614-name-388" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BARNES</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the prisoner running in Weymouth-place, close to Devonshire-place—he had a loaf under his jacket, eating it as he me along—he was taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410614-name-389" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410614-name-389" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410614-name-389" type="surname" value="BLAKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410614-name-389" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BLAKE</persName>
                  </hi>. I was a policeman at that time. I took the prisoner—I said, "You are the lad that stole a loaf;" he said, "I have not seen one to-day"—I took him to the station—he said if the baker would say no more about it he would pay for it.</p>
